reason.tex:
%text Remember \[ \qquad \sin^{-1} (\sin x) \neq \dfrac{1}{\sin}\cdot \sin x\] Similarly \[ \qquad \cos\left( \cos^{-1}x \right) \neq \cos\cdot\dfrac{1}{\cos} x\] The above statements are meaningless The ones below are however true -- and follow \underline\text{straight from the definition}
% \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{MMM}
\hline \textbf{If} & \textbf{Then} & \textbf{Also } \\ \hline \sin\theta = x & \sin^{-1}(\sin \theta) = \theta & \sin(\sin^{-1}x) = x \\ \hline \cos\theta = x & \cos^{-1}(\cos \theta) = \theta & \cos(\cos^{-1}x) = x \\ \hline \tan\theta = x & \tan^{-1}(\tan \theta) = \theta & \tan(\tan^{-1}x) = x \\ \hline \csc\theta = x & \csc^{-1}(\csc\theta) = \theta & \csc(\csc^{-1}x) = x \\ \hline \sec\theta = x & \sec^{-1}(\sec \theta) = \theta & \sec(\sec^{-1}x) = x \\ \hline \cot\theta = x & \cot^{-1}(\cot \theta) = \theta & \cot(\cot^{-1}x) = x \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
